info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 26 at 1:38AM MST until December 27 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 2 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 8 PM MST TUESDAY... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 50 mph with gusts up to 80 mph. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County. * WHEN...2 PM Monday afternoon until 8 PM Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight and high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
